  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Rights-Based Solutions For Vulnerable Migrants through a Migrant Resource and Response Mechanism (MRRM) in the South of Libya</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The risky and complex journeys undertaken by migrants, reaching Libya and beyond, expose them as well as host communities to multiple health risks. Due to the continuous and prolonged instability the health system is fragmented, ineffective and lacks the ability to respond to health needs of not only thousands of migrants but also the Libyan population. The health needs of these vulnerable migrants are rarely met due to barriers in accessing the services and other health system issues in Libya. The situation in the south of Libya is even more severe than the overall conditions of the healthcare system. Through this project, IOM is providing multi-sectoral support to migrants and vulnerable populations in Ghat though its mobile multi-service provision mechanism &#x2013; Migrants Resource and Response Mechanism (MRRM). Beneficiaries are receiving primary health care services, non-food items and hygiene kits, protection services and referral to various more specialised types of assistance. Simultaneously, IOM is disseminating information materials about the risks of irregular migration and working towards increased acceptance of migrants by the local community through the implementation of a community cohesion initiative.</narrative>
  </description>
